We first need to calculate ROA using the net profit and the total assets at the end of the period. In this case:

• Net Profit = 1,193,771.08  
• Total Assets (End_amount) = 15,023,526.85

ROA is calculated using the formula:  
  ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100%

Now, plug in the numbers:

  ROA = (1,193,771.08 / 15,023,526.85) × 100%  
     = 0.07945 × 100%  
     = 7.945%

Rounded to two decimal places, the ROA is approximately 7.95%.

Thus, the solution in the requested format is:

{"solution": {'Return on Assets (ROA)': '7.95%'} }
